  "fun_fact": "Over 60% of India's farmland has soil organic carbon below 0.5% — less than a third of the healthy threshold — largely due to decades of synthetic fertiliser overuse. Switching back from chemical to natural farming is not easy, but it's possible. In 2016, Sikkim became the first state in the world to be certified 100% organic. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ySgbWcYttaQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Know more</a>",
